				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Probably in part due to taunt, in part due to root.  While the mob is rooted, its probably going after the BL pet for the above mentioned proxy-aggro reasons.
<br />

<br />
But being noticably lower level is a pretty sizable taunt, at least for PCs.  That's probably why the BL <span style="font-style: italic">consistantly</span> keeps aggro, as opposed to pinging around between roots.  I've duoed with a necro a decent bit, and using Earth or Air my (lower level, by 1-2 spell circles) would maintain aggro most of the time.  Looking back, it's not that great of an experiment - the high taunt stun pet, and the proxy-aggro-instigating Earth pet - but its still something.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
