			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm going with the idea of lower level = more aggro.  Mobs ARE coded somehow to take out the weakest link first--it's the same reasoning behind why low health generates aggro.  As a melee gains levels, they're able to control their aggro a tad better just because they're higher level in relation to the mobs at that point.  The lowest level character in a group (especially melees) generally gets beat on a lot in most situations.  If ya ever notice, using epic pet in a group full of pet users 61+ means that epic pet will be the tank 99% of the time.  It almost always happens.  Many could attribute that to his proc rate, but I would say his lower level just gets him the attention as well.  Change out Rathe's Son in that situation with another pet, like Ward of Xegony.  He stuns and such, so he should keep a lot of aggro--right?  I would guarantee that the BST pet would still keep aggro over Ward.  
<br />

<br />
Also, BST warders have their own innate procs.  They generate a LOT of aggro in relation to other pets.  I would very much compare the epic pet's proc to that of the BST warder's rate, because they both go off an extreme amount.  If your friend stopped using his proc buffs, that might also fix the problem of his pet outaggroing.  
<br />

<br />
All of the above, coupled with the fact rooted mobs change the rules of aggro completely, could be causing problems.
<br />

<br />
One more thing... I have noticed Host of the Elements WILL get aggro if I don't give my pet a few seconds to solo and build aggro on a mob.  Try to time them so the pet has only attacked the mob for around 3 seconds and have Host on that mob.  Host will definately outaggro Rathe's Son, or any other pet you have on the mob at that time.  While soloing I find Host is more of a damage mitigator (it takes a few seconds for the mob to wipe out all 9 of them, thus alleviating a few rounds of damage from my main pet) than anything else.<br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062" taret=_blank>Sage Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a>
<br />
Arch Convoker of Solusek Ro
<br />
<a href="http://www.furiouspantaloons.org"><i>Furious Pantaloons</i></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
